location: Sam Boyd Stadium, Las Vegas, NV

videos.description: With a 31-28 win over Toledo, Appalachian State wins the Raycom Media Camellia Bowl for the second year in a row. The Mountaineers end the season with a 10-3 record.
videos.title: FBS Football: Appalachian State wins the Camellia Bowl

videos.description: Southern Miss beats Louisiana-Lafayette 28-21 to win their fourth R+L Carriers New Orleans Bowl victory. Allenzae Staggers set a New Orleans Bowl record with 230 receiving yards for the Golden Eagles.
videos.title: FBS Football: Southern Mississippi wins the New Orleans Bowl

videos.description: Tulsa wins the Miami Beach Bowl 55-10 over Central Michigan. Tulsa QB Dane Evans passed for 304 yards and 5 touchdowns.
videos.title: FBS Football: Tulsa wins the Miami Beach Bowl

videos.description: Western Kentucky wins the Boca Raton Bowl 51-31 over Memphis. Hilltopper RB Anthony Wales set a career-high 245 yards and scored 3 touchdowns.
videos.title: FBS Football: Western Kentucky wins the Boca Raton Bowl

videos.description: BYU wins a rainy Poinsettia Bowl 24-21 against Wyoming. Jamaal Williams led the way for the Cougars with 210 rushing yards in his final game.
videos.title: FBS Football: BYU wins the Poinsettia Bowl

videos.description: Idaho wins the Famous Idaho Potato Bowl 61-50 over Colorado State. Quarterback Matt Linehan led the way for the Vandals with 381 yards passing and 5 total touchdowns.
videos.title: FBS Football: Idaho wins the Famous Idaho Potato Bowl

videos.description: Old Dominion win its first ever bowl game with a 24-20 win over Eastern Michigan in the Popeyes Bahamas Bowl. David Washington led the way for the Monarchs with three touchdown passes.
videos.title: FBS Football: Old Dominion wins the Popeyes Bahamas Bowl

videos.description: Louisiana Tech win a shootout against Navy 48-45 in the Armed Forces Bowl. Trent Turner was the games' MVP with 233 receiving yards and 2 touchdowns.
videos.title: FBS Football: Louisiana Tech wins the Armed Forces Bowl

location: Amon G. Carter Stadium, Fort Worth, TX
Hawaiian Tel Federal Credit Union Field, Honolulu, HI

videos.description: Mississippi State wins the St. Petersburg Bowl, slipping past Miami (Ohio) 17-16. DL Nelson Adams blocked the RedHawks field goal in the 4th quarter, giving the Bulldogs the win.
videos.title: FBS Football: Mississippi State wins the St. Petersburg Bowl

videos.description: Boston College holds off Maryland 36-30 to win the Quick Lane Bowl. This was the Eagles first bowl game win in nine years.
videos.title: FBS Football: Boston College wins the Quick Lane Bowl

videos.description: N.C. State dominated Vanderbilt 41-17, winning the Camping World Independence Bowl. Junior TE/FB Jaylen Samuels finished the game with 6 catches and 104 receiving yards.
videos.title: FBS Football: N.C. State wins the Camping World Independence Bowl

videos.description: Wake Forest upsets Temple, 34-26, to win the Military Bowl Presented by Northrop Grumman. This marks the Demon Deacons first bowl victory and winning season since 2008.
videos.title: FBS Football: Wake Forest wins the Military Bowl Presented by Northrop Grumman

location: Navy-Marine Corps Memorial Stadium, Annapolis, MD

videos.description: Minnesota upsets Washington State, 17-12, to win the National Funding Holiday Bowl. This is the first time the Gophers have won 9 games in one season since 2003.
videos.title: FBS Football: Minnesota wins the National Funding Holiday Bowl

videos.description: Miami upsets West Virginia 31-14, winning the Russell Athletic Bowl. This marks the Hurricanes first bowl win since 2006.
videos.title: FBS Football: Miami wins the Russell Athletic Bowl

videos.description: Utah edges past Indiana with a late field goal to win the Foster Farms Bowl 26-24. Joe Williams set a Foster Farms Bowl record with 222 yards rushing.
videos.title: FBS Football: Utah wins the Foster Farms Bowl

videos.description: Kansas State defeats Texas A&M 33-28 in the Advocare V100 Texas Bowl. The victory is Kansas State's second bowl win since 2002.
videos.title: FBS Football: Kansas State wins the Texas Bowl

videos.description: After heading into overtime, South Florida wins the Birmingham Bowl 46-39 over South Carolina. Bulls QB Quinton Flowers totaled 366 yards of offense and 5 touchdowns.
videos.title: FBS Football: South Florida wins the Birmingham Bowl

videos.description: Virginia Tech scores 35 unanswered points in the second half to beat Arkansas, 35-24 in the Belk Bowl. Jerod Evans scored four touchdowns, and broke the Virginia Tech record for most rushing yards in a season by a quarterback.
videos.title: FBS Football: Virginia Tech wins the Belk Bowl

location: Bank of America Stadium, Charlotte, NC

videos.description: Georgia wins the AutoZone Liberty Bowl 31-23 over TCU. This game marks the Bulldogs 30th win, putting them in third place for the most bowl wins in NCAA history.
videos.title: FBS Football: Georgia wins the AutoZone Liberty Bowl

location: Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium, Memphis, TN
Sun Bowl Stadium, El Paso, TX

videos.description: Tennessee wins the Franklin American Mortgage Music City Bowl 38-24 over Nebraska. In his final game as a Vol, Joshua Dobbs had four touchdowns and 291 passing yards.
videos.title: FBS Football: Tennessee wins the Music City Bowl

location: Hard Rock Stadium, Miami Gardens, FL

videos.description: Georgia Tech outruns Kentucky to win the Taxslayer Bowl 33-18. Dedrick Mills led the Yellow Jackets' attack with 169 rushing yards and a touchdown.
videos.title: FBS Football: Georgia Tech wins the Taxslayer Bowl

videos.description: Alabama wins the Chick-fil-A Peach Bowl 24-7 over Washington. Alabama continues their undefeated season and will compete for their second straight National Championship.
videos.title: FBS Football: Alabama wins the Peach Bowl

location: University of Phoenix Stadium, Glendale, AZ
